      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 18: Setting CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET to 13.0 unconditionally changes the minimum supported macOS version for every Apple build, which is a user-visible compatibility regression unrelated to adding a macOS 26 icon. Keep the previous deployment target unless the project has explicitly decided to drop older macOS support, or gate only the asset-catalog generation on the required toolchain. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nif(APPLE AND NOT DEFINED CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET)\n  set(CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET \"11.0\" CACHE STRING \"Minimum macOS version\")\nendif()\n```",
